LINE.Text: In 1990, there were 50 centenarians in Singapore. By 2015, that number had multiplied
to 1,100 and continues to grow. As life expectancy rises, the ability to live long and
well is increasingly linked to a number of lifestyle factors that include our relationships,
health and wellness, financial habits, and opportunities and attitudes at work.
With these factors in mind, The Economist Intelligence Unit surveyed 1,214 of Singapore's
residents on their preparedness for longevity. How ready are they to live to 100?
